Let $r$ be the radius of the sphere.  Let $O = (0,0,r)$ and $P = (3,0,1).$  We take a cross-section.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

real r = 9/4;
pair O = (0,r), P = (3,1), T = interp(O,P,r/(r + 1));

draw((-4,0)--(4,0));
draw(Circle(P,1));
draw(Circle((-3,1),1));
draw(Circle(O,r));
draw(O--(0,0));
draw(O--P);
draw((3,1)--(0,1));
draw((3,1)--(3,0));

label("$r$", (O + T)/2, N);
label("$1$", (T + P)/2, N);
